⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Dmitri Razumikhin
node CRP · CRP · ⟦Dmitri Razumikhin:CRP:63b778⟧

WHO   — Dmitri Razumikhin — the friend · ordinary goodness
WHAT  — The novel's healthy heart: poor like Rodion but generous, energetic, and decent — the life Raskolnikov could have had.
WHERE — CRP · Crime and Punishment  Framework inputs: Crime and Punishment (Dostoevsky, 1866)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the book's darkness needs one figure of plain, active kindness to measure the rest against.
HOW   — By loyalty, labour, good humour, and a furious common-sense rant against reducing men to theories.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am no Napoleon and never wanted to be — I work, I love my friends, and that ordinary decency is the thing the theory despised.

